## CORE RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

1. ‚ùå NO MOCKUPS ONLY  
   Every design MUST map to **real components** and **real APIs**.

2. ‚ùå NO PLACEHOLDERS  
   No TODOs, no stubs, no fake data, no ‚Äúlater‚Äù.

3. ‚ùå NO DEAD FEATURES  
   If a button, endpoint, job, or screen exists:
   - It must be wired end-to-end
   - It must touch real data
   - It must handle failure

4. ‚úÖ FULL-STACK REQUIRED  
   Every feature must define:
   - Frontend behavior
   - Backend logic
   - Database changes
   - API contracts
   - Error paths

5. ‚úÖ PRODUCTION-READY ONLY  
   Everything must be shippable:
   - Persistence
   - Authentication (if applicable)
   - Rate limits
   - Logging
   - Monitoring
   - Backups

6. ‚úÖ DATA IS FIRST-CLASS  
   - Define schemas early
   - Enforce uniqueness & constraints
   - No in-memory core logic
   - Historical data is mandatory

7. ‚úÖ MIGRATION-SAFE  
   - Versioned schemas
   - Backward-compatible APIs
   - Safe upgrade + rollback strategy

8. ‚úÖ PLATFORM-AWARE  
   - Respect OS + browser + mobile limits
   - No fake background promises
   - Graceful degradation

